# Next.js Rules (extends 00-core.mdc)

## Component Model
- Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only for interactive leaf components or browser-only APIs.
- Keep domain logic in `src/features/`, `src/server/`, or `src/lib/` — not in page or route files.
- Prefer server-side data fetching. Avoid client-side waterfalls from nested fetches.

## Route Handlers
- Keep route handlers thin: validate input via schema → call service → return typed response.
- Do not bury business logic in `route.ts` or `page.tsx`.

## Splitting
- If a page component exceeds 200 lines, extract data-fetching into server functions and UI into child components.
- One component per file when reused or exceeds 80 lines.

## Quality
- Run `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test && npm run build` after changes.
- Check `docs/commands.md` for exact commands.
